	(text "NUCLEO-N657X0-Q Gateway interconnect\nUsing NUCLEO CN3 and CN15 only\n\nNUCLEO is the SPI5 master.\nDWM3001CDK and XIAO ESP32-C6 share SPI5 SCK / MISO / MOSI.\nEach peripheral has its own chip-select and control/interrupt lines.\n\nCN15 signal header\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCN15.11  PE15 / SPI5_SCK    ----+--> DWM3001CDK J10.23  SPI1_CLK\n                                 +--> XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 9   D8 / SCK\n\nCN15.13  PG1  / SPI5_MISO   <---+--- DWM3001CDK J10.21  SPI1_MISO\n                                 +--- XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 10  D9 / MISO\n\nCN15.15  PG2  / SPI5_MOSI   ----+--> DWM3001CDK J10.19  SPI1_MOSI\n                                 +--> XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 11  D10 / MOSI\n\nCN15.17  PA3  / DWM_CS      -------> DWM3001CDK J10.24  CS_RPI\nCN15.16  PB9  / DWM_IRQ     <------- DWM3001CDK J10.15  GPIO_RPI\nCN15.33  PD0  / DWM_RESET   -------> DWM3001CDK J10.12  RESET\n\nCN15.19  PD7  / C6_CS       -------> XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 4   D3 / GPIO21\nCN15.5   PC1  / C6_INT      <------- XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 3   D2 / GPIO2\n\n\nCN3 power / auxiliary header\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCN3.6    5V / 5V_NUCLEO     ----+--> DWM3001CDK J10.2 or J10.4  5V0 / VRPI\n                                +--> XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 14       VBUS / 5V\n\nCN3.16   3V3 / 3V3_C6       -------> 3.3 V pull-up / auxiliary rail\n                                      Feeds pull-up resistors and local 3.3 V caps only.\n                                      Does not power XIAO pin 12.\n\nCN3.8    GND                ----+--> DWM3001CDK GND\nCN3.19   GND                ----+--> DWM3001CDK GND\nCN3.20   GND                ----+--> XIAO ESP32-C6 pin 13  GND\nCN3.22   GND                ----+--> common GND\n\nCN15.9   GND                -------> common GND\nCN15.20  GND                -------> common GND\n\n\nXIAO ESP32-C6 power note\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nXIAO ESP32-C6 pin 14 VBUS / 5V is powered from NUCLEO 5V_NUCLEO.\nXIAO ESP32-C6 pin 13 GND is connected to common GND.\nXIAO ESP32-C6 pin 12 3V3 is not used as a power input in this design.\nPlace a KiCad no-connect flag on XIAO pin 12.\n\n\nOptional / parked\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCN3.17   PC0 / C6_EN_RST    Optional future XIAO EN / CHIP_PU control.\n                            Leave NC unless the XIAO EN pad is deliberately wired."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
